# ─── GitHub OAuth ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a GitHub OAuth App at: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Homepage URL:       https://your-app.vercel.app
# Callback URL:       https://your-app.vercel.app/api/auth
#
# Then set these in Vercel project settings → Environment Variables:
#   GITHUB_CLIENT_ID     (server-side, used in api/auth.js)
#   GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET (server-side, used in api/auth.js)
#   APP_ORIGIN           (server-side, e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app)
#
# And this in your local .env (prefix VITE_ so Vite exposes it to the browser):
VITE_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_oauth_app_client_id
